		<td><b>Bankswitching question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is probably my newbie-ist question yet.
<br />
<br />When you do a bankswitch (like on an UNROM)  is there any delay  associated with it?
<br />
<br />   I'm 99.9% sure that the only cost is the actual  CPU instruction costs (LDA , STA etc..)  but I still wanted to check because I know some calls  cost a lot more in CPU cycles than the actual  instruction. (like STA 4014 to invoke Sprite DMA which costs at least 512 CPU cycles)   
<br />
<br />Al

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>kyuusaku</b> [ Thu Nov 08, 2007 2:35 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There is the delay in the form of logic gate propagation time, but the outputs in all commercial mapper stabilize long before even the next half-CPU cycle.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
